otherCitationDetails.gco:CharacterString: Historic aerial photos of Wisconsin dated 1937-1941

abstract.gco:CharacterString: The Wisconsin Historic Aerial Image Finder provides free online access to over 38,000 aerial photographs of Wisconsin from 1937-41. These photographs were originally acquired by the US Department of Agriculture. As part of a three-year project funded by the Ira and Ineva Reilly Baldwin Wisconsin Idea Endowment at the University of Wisconsin-Madison, these photographs were scanned, indexed, and made web-accessible through a map-based interface. The aerial photos are available for download by any user without fee or use restrictions.

purpose.gco:CharacterString: The Wisconsin Historic Aerial Image Finder provides free online access to over 38,000 aerial photographs of Wisconsin from 1937-41. While the individual images are not georeferenced, full-resolution (600dpi) TIFFs are available for download.

supplementalInformation.gco:CharacterString: Aerial photos range in years from 1937-1941. The most complete collections of historic images were digitized for each county. Years may vary by county. Photograph scale is 1:20,000. Images are black and white.
